This program should be used on your own responsibility. Redpine Signals assumes no responsibility for any losses incurred by customers or third parties arising from the use of this file.
===========================================================================================================
=========================================================================================================== Function description: =========================================================================================================== This example demonstrate ADC power consumption for single channel data acquisition with 100ksps sampling rate. Here ADC internal DMA use for data collection from ADC FIFO.Following configuration used in application, 1.Sampling rate : 100ksps. 2.Input type : Single ended. 3.Positive input to ADC : ULP_GPIO4 4.Negative input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5,For single ended data acquisition this parameter not used. 5.Reference Voltage : 3.2V (Bypass LDO)(To change reference voltage modify 'vref_value' variable #line31) 6.Number of sample collection for each interrupt : 1023 7.ADC output memory : Ping memory : 0x24060800 Pong memory : 0x24060800 + (Number of sample collection for each interrupt * 2) =========================================================================================================== Environment =========================================================================================================== Test Board: --------------------- Smark EVK Rev1.2
Assistance software: --------------------- None
=========================================================================================================== Usage Procedure: =========================================================================================================== Compile and Run the example. In single ended mode give the input to ULP_GPIO_4 and in differential ended mode give positive input to ULP_GPIO4 and negative input to ULP_GPIO5. =========================================================================================================== Pass criteria: =========================================================================================================== This example demonstrate power consumption of ADC in 1ksps as sampling rate. 1. Power pass criteria : a.Define "DONOT_READ_DATA_FROM_MEM" macro in (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define) M4 will not read the ADC samples for memory. b.Disable the 'ENOB' macro (In adc_100ksps_power_save.c #30) Result : 1.ADC 100Ksps power consumption(Input supply for chip 3.2v) : 297uA 2.ADC 100Ksps power consumption(Input supply for chip 1.8v) : 549uA
2. Performance pass criteria : For verifying performance follow below step , a.Enable the 'ENOB' macro (In adc_100ksps_power_save.c #30) b.Disable or remove "DONOT_READ_DATA_FROM_MEM" macro form (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define) M4 will read the ADC samples for memory. c.Apply the following configuration input waveform from waveform generator to ADC. 1]Differential Mode(3.2) 1.Vpp(Magnitude) : (3.2*0.6) = 1.92V 2.Vcm(Offset) : (3.2*0.5) = 1.6V 3.Input frequency : 10Khz 2]Differential Mode(1.8) 1.Vpp(Magnitude) : (1.8*0.6) = 1.08V 2.Vcm(Offset) : (1.8*0.5) = 0.9V 3.Input frequency : 10Khz 3]Single ended Mode(3.2) 1.Vpp(Magnitude) : (3.2) = 3.2V 2.Vcm(Offset) : (3.2*0.5) = 1.6V 3.Input frequency : 10Khz 4]Single ended Mode(1.8) 1.Vpp(Magnitude) : (1.8) = 1.8V 2.Vcm(Offset) : (1.8*0.5) = 0.9V 3.Input frequency : 10Khz d.Apply the FFT on adc_output buffer samples. e.After apply FFT following SNR will get form application 1.Differential ended SNR(Input supply for chip 3.2v ) : 55dB 2.Single ended SNR(Input supply for chip 3.2v ) : 51dB 3.Differential ended SNR(Input supply for chip 1.8v ) : 54dB 4.Single ended SNR(Input supply for chip 1.8v ) : 49dB =========================================================================================================== Note =========================================================================================================== 1]For power consumption measurement a.Define "DONOT_READ_DATA_FROM_MEM" macro in (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define) M4 will not read the ADC samples for memory. b.Disable the 'ENOB' macro (In adc_10ksps_power_save.c #30) 2]For performance measurement a.Enable the 'ENOB' macro (In adc_10ksps_power_save.c #30) b.Disable or remove "DONOT_READ_DATA_FROM_MEM" macro form (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define) M4 will read the ADC samples for memory. ===========================================================================================================

=============================================================================================== ADC maximum sampling rate example =============================================================================================== Copyright(C) Redpine Signals 2016 All rights reserved by Redpine Signals.
This program should be used on your own responsibility. Redpine Signals assumes no responsibility for any losses incurred by customers or third parties arising from the use of this file.
===============================================================================================
=============================================================================================== Function description: =============================================================================================== Inherent sampling rate limit for single ADC channel is 2.5Msps but ADC can be work till 5Msps sampling rate,So for 5msps sampling rate need to enable two ADC channel with same sampling rate and same channel configuration Enable "MAX_SAMPLING_RATE"(in rsi_adc.h) macro or define in (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define) Enable "MULTICHANNEL_ENABLE"(in rsi_adc.h) macro or define in (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define)
following configuration used in example for channel0 and channel1: 1.Sampling rate : 2.5Msps (Each channel 2.5Msps ,Effective sampling rate 5Msps) 2.Input type : Single ended. 3.Positive input to ADC : ULP_GPIO4 4.Negative input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5,For single ended data acquisition this parameter not used. 5.Reference Voltage : 2.8V (On LDO)(To change reference voltage modify 'vref_value' variable #line29) 6.Number of sample collection for each interrupt : 1024 =============================================================================================== Environment =============================================================================================== Test Board: --------------------- Smart EVK Rev1.2
Assistance software: --------------------- None =============================================================================================== MACRO usage =============================================================================================== 1.'MAX_SAMPLING_RATE'(#line35 in rsi_adc.h file) Enable this macro to collect the ADC samples at 5Msps sampling rate.
2.'CORE_CLOCK_180MHZ' Enable this macro as one to switch M4 clock to 180Mhz.
3.'NUMBER_OF_CHA_EN' Make this macro as two to enable two ADC channel.
4.'CHANNEL_SAMPLE_LENGTH' Sample to collect of each iteration. maximum samples can be collect 1024.
5.'PS2_STATE_ADC_DATA_AQU_ENABLE' Make this macro as one if code is running in PS2 state. Make this MACRO as zero for PS4 state and flash based execution. =============================================================================================== Usage Procedure: =============================================================================================== Give the input to ULP_GPIO_4 for single ended mode. Give the positive input on ULP_GPIO_4 and negative input on ULP_GPIO_5 in differential mode. =============================================================================================== Pass criteria: ===================================================================================================== Enable the ENOB macro so after 10 interrupt iteration M4 will stop execution and read samples from 'adc_output_result[]' buffer and calculate SNR on output data. ===================================================================================================== Note ===================================================================================================== 2.Disable gain and offset calculation on ADC samples comments '#define GAIN_OFFSET_CAL_EN'(#line39 in rsi_adc.h file). 3.Comments '#define PS2_STATE_ADC_DATA_AQU_ENABLE'(#line38 in rsi_adc.h file). =====================================================================================================

=============================================================================================== ADC Multichannel Example =============================================================================================== Copyright(C) Redpine Signals 2016 All rights reserved by Redpine Signals.
This program should be used on your own responsibility. Redpine Signals assumes no responsibility for any losses incurred by customers or third parties arising from the use of this file.
===============================================================================================
=============================================================================================== Function description: =============================================================================================== Enable the multiple ADC channel with different or same configuration.In this example four ADC channel configure with different sampling rate.
following configuration used in example for channel0: 1.Sampling rate : 1.2Msps 2.Input type : Single ended. 3.Positive input to ADC : ULP_GPIO4 4.Negative input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5,For single ended data acquisition this parameter not used. 5.Reference Voltage : 2.8V (On LDO)(To change reference voltage modify 'vref_value' variable #line29) 6.Number of sample collection for each interrupt : 1024 9.Input Voltage range : 0.0V to 2.8V
following configuration used in example for channel1: 1.Sampling rate : 625Ksps 2.Input type : Single ended. 3.Positive input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5 4.Negative input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5,For single ended data acquisition this parameter not used. 5.Reference Voltage : 2.8V (On LDO)(To change reference voltage modify 'vref_value' variable #line29) 6.Number of sample collection for each interrupt : 1024 9.Input Voltage range : 0.0V to 2.8V
following configuration used in example for channel2: 1.Sampling rate : 156Ksps 2.Input type : Single ended. 3.Positive input to ADC : ULP_GPIO6 4.Negative input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5,For single ended data acquisition this parameter not used. 5.Reference Voltage : 2.8V (On LDO)(To change reference voltage modify 'vref_value' variable #line29) 6.Number of sample collection for each interrupt : 1024 9.Input Voltage range : 0.0V to 2.8V
following configuration used in example for channel3: 1.Sampling rate : 156Ksps 2.Input type : Single ended. 3.Positive input to ADC : ULP_GPIO7 4.Negative input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5,For single ended data acquisition this parameter not used. 5.Reference Voltage : 2.8V (On LDO)(To change reference voltage modify 'vref_value' variable #line29) 6.Number of sample collection for each interrupt : 1024 9.Input Voltage range : 0.0V to 2.8V
For configuring multiple channel sampling rate follow below guidelines, 1.Maximum sampling rate for single channel is 2.5Msps 2.To configure enabled ADC channels sampling rate,Channel[0] must be highest sampling rate and reaming channels sampling rate should be less then or equal channel0 sampling rate. For example , If i = (channel number) , Sampling rate of Channel[i] = (Channel[i-1] or (Channel[i-1]/2) or (Channel[i-1]/4) so on) e.g i = 2; then Sampling rate of Channel[2] = (Channel[2-1] or (Channel[2-1]/2) or (Channel[2-1]/4) so on).
Read the 1.achived_sampling_rate[0] = Configured channel0 sampling rate to ADC. 2.achived_sampling_rate[1] = Configured channel1 sampling rate to ADC. 3.achived_sampling_rate[2] = Configured channel2 sampling rate to ADC. 4.achived_sampling_rate[3] = Configured channel3 sampling rate to ADC. =============================================================================================== Environment =============================================================================================== Test Board: --------------------- Smart EVK Rev1.2
Assistance software: --------------------- None =============================================================================================== MACRO usage =============================================================================================== 1.'MULTICHANNEL_ENABLE'(#line41 in rsi_adc.h file) Enable macro for multiple channel data acquisition,here MULTICHANNEL_ENABLE already define in (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define)
2.'PS2_STATE_ADC_DATA_AQU_ENABLE'(#line38 in rsi_adc.h file) Enable this macro if code is running in PS2 state. Enable this macro for PS4 state and flash based execution.
3.'CORE_CLOCK_180MHZ' Enable this macro as one to switch M4 clock to 180Mhz.
4.'NUMBER_OF_CHA_EN' Number of channel enable for data acquisition.
5.'CHANNEL0_SAMPLE_LENGTH' Sample to collect for channel0. maximum samples can be collect 1024.
6.'CHANNEL1_SAMPLE_LENGTH' Sample to collect for channel1. maximum samples can be collect 1024.
7.'CHANNEL2_SAMPLE_LENGTH' Sample to collect for channel2. maximum samples can be collect 1024.
8.'CHANNEL3_SAMPLE_LENGTH' Sample to collect for channel3. maximum samples can be collect 1024. =============================================================================================== Pass criteria: =============================================================================================== Enable ENOB macro to verify channels functionality,here after enabling ENOB macro code will stop after collecting 2048 samples for each channels. Read adc_channel0_result[] for channel0 data. Read adc_channel1_result[] for channel1 data. Read adc_channel2_result[] for channel2 data. Read adc_channel3_result[] for channel3 data.
Disable ENOB macro and process each channel 1024 samples. =============================================================================================== Note : =============================================================================================== 1.Make this macro as one for multiple channel data acquisition,here MULTICHANNEL_ENABLE already define in (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define) 2.For PS2 state data acquisition make '#define PS2_STATE_ADC_DATA_AQU_ENABLE'(#line38 in rsi_adc.h file) ===============================================================================================

=============================================================================================== Function description: =============================================================================================== In this example single ADC channel will collect configured number of samples.Here following configuration are used in application: 1.Sampling rate : 100Ksps. 2.Input type : Single ended. 3.Positive input to ADC : ULP_GPIO4 4.Negative input to ADC : ULP_GPIO5,For single ended data acquisition this parameter not used. 5.Reference Voltage : 2.8V (On LDO)(To change reference voltage modify 'vref_value' variable #line36) 6.Number of sample collection for each interrupt : 1023 7.ADC output memory : Ping memory : 0x24060800 Pong memory : 0x24060800 + (Number of sample collection for each interrupt * 2)
In this example ADC output can be process in FIR low pass filter so enable 'FIR_FILTER_ENABLE'(#line 34) to process ADC output in FIR filter.
FIR Filter Specification : 1.'FILTER_COEFF_23_Q15' : If this macro enable then 23 filter coeff used for FIR filter operation,Following configuration used in this filter, a.Fs(Sampling rate) : 5Mhz b.Pass band ripple : 1dB c.Stop band attenuation : 20dB d.Fc(cut off frequency) : 100Khz e.Fstop(stop band frequency) : 300Khz Enable '#define FILTER_COEFF_23_Q15 1'(#line 55) for above filter.
1.'FILTER_COEFF_88_Q15' : If this macro enable then 88 filter coeff used for FIR filter operation,Following configuration used in this filter, a.Fs(Sampling rate) : 5Mhz b.Pass band ripple : 1dB c.Stop band attenuation : 20dB d.Fc(cut off frequency) : 25Khz e.Fstop(stop band frequency) : 75Khz Enable '#define FILTER_COEFF_88_Q15 1'(#line 56) for above filter. =============================================================================================== Environment =============================================================================================== Test Board: --------------------- Smart EVK Rev1.2
Assistance software: --------------------- None =============================================================================================== MACRO usage =============================================================================================== 1.'GAIN_OFFSET_CAL_EN'(#line39 in rsi_adc.h) Enable the gain and offset calculation on ADC samples,Enable this macro for printing input equivalent voltage.here GAIN_OFFSET_CAL_EN already define in (Options for Target --> C/C++ -->Define)
3.'FIR_FILTER_ENABLE'(#line34 in adc_single_chnl_example.c) Enable this macro as one to apply the low pass filter on ADC output.
4.'CORE_CLOCK_180MHZ'(#line28 in adc_single_chnl_example.c) Enable this macro as one to switch M4 clock to 180Mhz.
5.'FINDOUT_INPUT_VOLTAGE'(#line35 in adc_single_chnl_example.c) Enable this macro as one for findout input to ADC based on ADC output samples. =============================================================================================== Usage Procedure: =============================================================================================== Give the input to ULP_GPIO_4 for single ended mode. Give the positive input on ULP_GPIO_4 and negative input on ULP_GPIO_5 in differential mode. =============================================================================================== Pass criteria: =============================================================================================== After enable 'FINDOUT_INPUT_VOLTAGE' M4 will store the equivalent input voltage from ADC output samples in 'adc_input_eqv_vltg' buffer.
Filter enable outputs for sine tone input 1.If FILTER_COEFF_23_Q15 = 1 In this filter max input tone can apply = Achieved sampling/50 (Cutoff freq is 100khz) E.g In this example sampling rate is 100ksps so max sine ton can apply 2Khz. Expected Result : FIR input samples SNR : 59.02dB FIR output samples SNR : 67.21dB
2.If FILTER_COEFF_88_Q15 = 1 In this filter max input tone can apply = Achieved sampling/200 (Cutoff freq is 25khz) E.g In this example sampling rate is 100ksps so max sine ton can apply 0.5Khz. Expected Result : FIR input samples SNR : 59.48dB FIR output samples SNR : 73.47dB =============================================================================================== Note =============================================================================================== 1.Make sure 'DONOT_READ_DATA_FROM_MEM'(#line37 in rsi_adc.h) is not enabled. 2.Make sure 'MULTICHANNEL_ENABLE'(#line41 in rsi_adc.h) is not enabled 4.Enable '#define GAIN_OFFSET_CAL_EN'(#line39 in rsi_adc.h) For dc precision application or else disable '#define GAIN_OFFSET_CAL_EN' macro. ===============================================================================================
